Conda is a package and environment Management tool:
------------------------------------------------------------
Create new environemnt
conda create -n yourenvname python=x.x anaconda
------------------------------------------------------------
Conda list the environments
conda list
------------------------------------------------------------
Remove Environment
conda remove -n myenv 
------------------------------------------------------------
Info on all the enviroments
conda info --envs
------------------------------------------------------------
Activate an environment
activate myenv 
------------------------------------------------------------
Version of the conda
conda --version
------------------------------------------------------------
Channel is the place where the conda can search for packages:
Displays the channels and their priority
conda config --get channels
------------------------------------------------------------
To search for all the channels for a package_name
conda search -f package_name
------------------------------------------------------------
To install a package from a channel mention the name of the channel with flag -c
conda install -c channel_name package_name
------------------------------------------------------------
To update all the packages of conda
conda update
------------------------------------------------------------
If a package is not available from the conda try pip
pip install pacakge_name
------------------------------------------------------------
If you donot want to update some of the packages:
1. Create a file named pinned inside the conda-meta directory
2. Mention the name of the package with version to be installed.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
